source: Tech confession: I can't wrap my head around Grafana & Prometheus, at least from a server/application metrics and monitoring standpoint.
translation: I understand your query. Although Grafana and Prometheus are important tools for monitoring server and application metrics, they can be complex to understand, especially from a beginner's point of view. Grafana is a web-based interface for visualising and exploring metadata from multiple data sources, including Prometheus metrics. Prometheus is an open-source systems and service monitoring solution that collects metrics from applications and machines, and stores it in a time-series database. It's designed to be flexible in terms of metrics collection and storage, as well as being able to support different types of targets (such as HTTP, TCP, or custom collectors). Though, Grafana and Prometheus appear to be more complex than some other monitoring tools, yet they offer a lot of functionality and customization options that can give you a deeper understanding of your application and infrastructure.
